{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17607104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17607104"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:20:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:20:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15948"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15948"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8639"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113951"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8639"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15948"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95966"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"6861"},{"type":"tags","id":"8459"},{"type":"tags","id":"8567"},{"type":"tags","id":"8739"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20684"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20687"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113951","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/113951"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe tongue surface contains different types of papillae that serve various functions in taste and mechanical processing of food.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly describes the distribution of lingual papillae on the tongue surface?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Circumvallate papillae are scattered across the anterior two-thirds","Filiform papillae are concentrated only at the tongue margins","Fungiform papillae form a V-shaped line at the posterior third","Foliate papillae are distributed across the entire dorsal surface","Fungiform papillae are scattered across the anterior two-thirds"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe tongue contains four types of papillae with specific distributions and functions. \u003Cstrong\u003EFungiform papillae\u003C/strong\u003E are scattered across the anterior two-thirds of the tongue and contain taste buds that detect sweet, salty, sour, bitter and umami tastes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECircumvallate papillae\u003C/strong\u003E form a V-shaped line at the posterior third of the tongue rather than being scattered across the anterior two-thirds. \u003Cstrong\u003EFiliform papillae\u003C/strong\u003E are the most numerous and distributed across the dorsal surface, not concentrated only at the tongue margins. They have no taste buds but provide mechanical and tactile functions, helping to grip and manipulate food. The statement about \u003Cstrong\u003Efungiform papillae\u003C/strong\u003E forming a V-shaped line at the posterior third incorrectly describes the distribution of circumvallate papillae. \u003Cstrong\u003EFoliate papillae\u003C/strong\u003E are found specifically on the lateral edges of the tongue rather than across the entire dorsal surface, and they contain taste buds that are particularly sensitive to sour tastes. Understanding the distribution of these papillae is important as it relates to their specific functions in taste sensation and food manipulation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The tongue has four types of papillae with distinct distributions: filiform, fungiform, circumvallate, and foliate","Each type of lingual papilla serves specific functions in taste and mechanical processing","Filiform 